WEBVTT

00:02.802 --> 00:05.303
Have you guys seen this feature
that lets you talk to Siri

00:05.305 --> 00:07.038
without pressing
any buttons?

00:07.040 --> 00:08.473
No. How does it work?

00:08.475 --> 00:11.910
You just say, uh, “Hey,
Siri, what time is it?”

00:11.912 --> 00:14.179
The time is 6:37 p.m.

00:14.181 --> 00:15.380
Yeah.

00:15.382 --> 00:17.615
So now anyone
can control your phone?

00:17.617 --> 00:20.852
Hey, Siri, show me pictures
of naked grandma butts.

00:20.854 --> 00:22.587
Nice try.

00:22.589 --> 00:25.790
It only recognizes <i>my</i> voice.
Oh. Cool.

00:25.792 --> 00:28.860
Hey, Siri, show me
pictures of naked grandma butts.

00:28.862 --> 00:31.863
I don't sound
like that.

00:31.865 --> 00:35.733
Here are some images
of naked grandma butts.

00:35.735 --> 00:38.136
Hey. Good news,
everybody.

00:38.138 --> 00:40.405
Now that I'm no longer
with Amy,

00:40.407 --> 00:43.341
I have an extra ticket to the
annual Thanksgiving lunch buffet

00:43.343 --> 00:46.010
at the aquarium cafeteria.
Who wants it?

00:48.580 --> 00:50.548
Well, you realize
you won't be going alone--

00:50.550 --> 00:52.216
I'll be there the whole time.

00:53.452 --> 00:56.020
Providing
fish and pilgrim facts.

00:57.456 --> 01:00.024
Can you people hear me?

01:00.026 --> 01:01.792
Well, we're having
everyone over.

01:01.794 --> 01:03.561
Yeah, Leonard and I
are gonna be cooking

01:03.563 --> 01:05.963
all day.
Otherwise we'd <i> love</i> to.

01:05.965 --> 01:07.131
But we can't.

01:07.133 --> 01:09.066
Yeah, poor us.
Mm-hmm.

01:11.536 --> 01:13.104
And Raj and I
are volunteering

01:13.106 --> 01:15.439
at the soup kitchen,
feeding food to the homeless.

01:15.441 --> 01:17.608
Well, Howard,
what about you?

01:17.610 --> 01:18.843
Oh...

01:18.845 --> 01:21.745
I can't. I'm going
to the soup kitchen, too.

01:21.747 --> 01:25.482
You said that sounded like
the worst thing ever.

01:26.985 --> 01:28.986
If you can't support me
when I'm lying,

01:28.988 --> 01:31.789
why are we married?

